canonical:
  title: 次茂朱寒風樓韻
  author: 金淡
  language: lzh
  text: 半在山崖半水邊柴門茅屋度年年版籍未删方外地巡遊如入洞中天浪傾太守丹霞液錯和諸公白雪篇共幕二郞先占句才名定合在盧前
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 次茂朱寒風樓韻
  author: 金淡
  language: lzh
  text: 半在山崖半水邊。柴門茅屋度年年。版籍未删方外地。巡遊如入洞中天。浪傾太守丹霞液。錯和諸公白雪篇。共幕二郞先占句。才名定合在盧前。
korean:
  title: 차 무주 한풍루 운
  author: 김담
  language: kor
  text: |-
    반은 산 벼랑에 걸치고, 반은 물 가에
    가시 사립문, 초가지붕 세월이 지났구나
    지적엔 세상밖이 땅도 들었는데
    찾아서 놀러오니 별유천지에 노니는 듯
    태수의 단하주를 부질없이 기울이면서
    여러분의 백설편을 그릇 회답하네
    같은 막부의 두 낭관이 먼저 시를 지으니
    그 재명 노조린 앞에 있을 만도하구나
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0200_010_0800&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 노조린(盧照隣) : '
    value: 당(唐)나라 왕발(王勃)이 양형(楊烱)ㆍ노조린(盧照隣)ㆍ낙빈왕(駱賓王)과 더불어 문장으로 이름을 날리니 세상에서 사걸(四傑)이라 일컬었다. 양형이 일찍이 말하되, “내가 노의 앞에 있음이 부끄럽고 왕의 뒤에 처함이 창피하노라.” 하였다.
english:
  title: Following the Rhyme of Master Muju's Cold Wind Pavilion
  author: Kim Dam
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Half clinging to the mountainside, half to the water's edge—
    A brushwood gate, a thatched roof: years pass in solitude.
    Though recorded in ledgers as beyond the world's reach,
    When visitors arrive, it becomes a separate heaven.

    I pour the Governor's crimson elixir to no avail,
    And clumsily respond to the refined verses of gentlemen.
    Yet as two scholars in the same pavilion compose first,
    Surely such talent must rank before even the luminaries.
  footnotes:
    - The poem follows the rhyme scheme of another work on the Cold Wind Pavilion (Hanpung-ru) in Muju, likely composed by a guest of higher literary standing.
    - The reference to 'two scholars in the same pavilion' (二郞) likely alludes to fellow literati of the time, with the final couplet playfully expressing modesty about his own poetic ability compared to more celebrated writers.
    - 盧照隣 (Lu Zhao-lin) was one of the Four Jades of early Tang poetry, celebrated alongside Wang Bo, Yang Jiong, and Luo Binwang—references that would have resonated deeply with educated Korean scholars of this period.
